I usually love this Whole Foods and have never had a problem. I actually drive 30 minutes just to come to this location, even though there’s one closer to my home, because the selection is better and the store is always clean and well-stocked.

But today, I had a disappointing experience at the coffee counter that left me feeling uneasy. I walked up to order and the older woman working there didn’t acknowledge me at all. She saw me standing there, walked away without saying a word, and left me waiting for about three minutes. When she returned, she still didn’t speak to me. She just asked another employee, “Is the coffee station closed?” He said yes, and she turned to me and said, “Yeah, we’re closed.”

No greeting. No apology for the wait. No effort to communicate respectfully.

It may not sound major, but as someone who shops here often and chooses to spend my time and money at this specific store, it made me feel unseen and dismissed. It’s the kind of interaction that makes you second-guess whether you’re truly welcome in a space, especially when basic courtesy is missing.

I hope this was just a one-off moment, but it was enough to make me look at this location a little differently.

reviews_data.review_text: My wife and I stopped in here to grab a quick dinner and find a few 🌽🍅🍎🍌🥐🍖 grocery items. The store seems totally revamped with really fun areas such as a 🍺 beer cave, bar, 🥪 deli, smoothie bar, 🧁🥯 bakery, and all the grocery aisles and sections you would expect from whole foods. This location also had decent indoor and excellent outdoor dining options. They also boasted ♿ handicap accessible 🅿️ parking, 🚻 restrooms, and seating. They also had ⚡ electric vehicle charging stations in the parking area.
Help attentive staff, good selection of products.   Will shop here again.

Nice quality items. They have real Italian prosciutto di Parma. The only ones in the area, so far. Got some Greek olives (non-pitted mix) which were very good. Good fresh rainbow trout. Prices are a bit high, but it's hard to tell nowadays... Everything is expensive. Clean, nice store.
